<subsection>
<title>Beneficiaries of Arduino </title>
<p>Arduino is a cool effective platform which makes everyone as a better developer. The beneficiaries of Arduino anyone who have interest to develop a new innovative product, however, it is meant for everyone</p>
<p>Arduino is mainly used for prototype model developing. The purpose of Arduino is to make learners learn and create projects/products using their innovative ideas. Arduino is recommended for its low cost and open-source platform where learners can easily learn the electronics and programming. As the development of the technologies increases the need for Arduino is also increasing. It is actively used for beginners, hobbyist and enthusiasts to develop mini-scale projects. In recent times electronics and electrical students have shown interested to use Arduino boards.</p>
<p>Today, academics and educational institutions are encouraging students to develop projects with the help of Arduino. Usage of Arduino in industrial productions has increased rapidly. The knowledge gained from here i.e.  Architecture of the micro controller, interfaces and external peripherals can be used in Industrial IOT.The fields like Farming, Healthcare and even a layman’s task is the active research areas of Arduino.</p>
<p><term>Characteristics of Arduino</term></p>
<p>Arduino is preferred platform for the following reasons </p>
<ul>
  <li> <term>Affordable –</term>Arduino is a low-cost board which is affordable for all. The cost of the Arduino is less than the other boards. Arduino clones are also available in reasonable prices.</li>
  <li> <term>Cross Platform- </term>Arduino is a cross platform which supports Arduino, Linux and Mac OS. </li>
  <li><term>Free and Open-Source Hardware-</term>complete guides to each Arduino board are published under Creative Common License.</li>
  <li><term>Free and Open-Source Software-</term>Arduino IDE official software is freely available to program the Arduino board.</li>
</ul>
