<p>Arduino Uno is a micro controller which controls the micro components. Works based on 32-bit micro controller. It acts as heart of the entire system. It has 6 Analog pins A0-A5 used as input pins, 14 digital pins 0-13, of which 6 pins are used as PWM (pulse width modulation). Digital pins used for both input and output. Arduino can be powered by USB cable or 9V volt battery if needed. It additionally has a 16 MHz ceramic resonator, power jack, ICSP header, 6 pins to program the boards firmware of the Arduino UNO consists of one inbuilt resistor and EEPROM Memory for storing the program.  Arduino UNO is also known as beginners kit for its robust feature in developing the products.  From the following figure 1.1.4, pin configuration of Arduino is explained in a pictorial representation. 	</p>
