  <p><term>NODE MCU </term></p>
  <p>NodeMCU is an open-source and development board specially made especially for IoT based Applications.  The NodeMCU ESP8266 development board has an inbuilt ESP-12E module. ESP8266 chip has Tensilica xtensa 32-bit LX106 RISC microprocessor.  It has a built in WIFI and Bluetooth module for higher end IOT applications. Node MCU supports real time operating system. It operates from 80 to 160 MHz clock frequency. Memory capacity up to 128 KB RAM and 4 MB of flash memory to store the data and program. It has 16 digital input and output pin (GPIO1- GPIO16) and has one Analog to Digital converter pin. Node MCU can be powered by VIN pin as external power supply and also by a micro-USB jack. It also supports UART, SPI and I2C interface.  There are two control pins EN, RST to reset the micro controller. Analog pin A0 to measure the voltage from 0-3.3V. Node MCU enables SPI serial peripheral interface communication between two controllers based on Master and slave protocol, SD1, CMD,SD0,CLK four pins are used for this purpose. The UART interface is to provide asynchronous communication. It communicates up to 4.5 Mbps speed and 4 pins for this purpose TXD0, RXD0, TXD2, RXD2.  From the below diagram clearly explains the pictorial representation of the NodeMCU. </p>

