  <p><term>Raspberry Pi -OS </term></p>
    <p>How to Install OS - Raspberry pi  </p>
    <p>Take 16 GB SD card and insert the SD card in slot dedicated for it. With the help of the browser, download the Raspbian OS from the official website <url href= "https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/" visual="https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/"></url> and open Thorny IDE software. Connect HDMI adapter from monitor, mouse and keyboard to the raspberry pi. Connect the ethernet cable from LAN adapter to raspberry pi .It also has an inbuilt WIFI and Bluetooth module to work with IOT applications. In Raspbian control panel, download GitHub clone to clone the projects in GitHub.  Board can be powered by micro-USB connector. When the board is powered, Raspbian OS get installed. </p>
  <p><term>After installing the OS, we can code the prototype with the help of Thonny IDE</term></p>
  <p><term>To install the python library, open the terminal and type</term> </p>
  <p>$ sudo apt -get install python -rpi.gpio python3 -rpi.gpio</p><p>after installing the python library, code the program in Thonny Python IDE.</p>
  <p><em><term>Raspberry Pi</term></em></p>
  <p>It is actually a small computer .It has 40 GPIO pins, for input and output purpose, HDMI adapter to connect to the monitor, 4 USB ports used to connect peripherals like keyboard, mouse. It also consists of ethernet port, to connect the board to internet. Operating voltage for the board is 5V and audio output is powered by 3.5mm audio jack port. It is typically used by computer and electronic hobbyists. SD card slot is used to insert the SD card.Camera port is used to connect camera with Raspberry Pi to work with image and video processing applications.  Although the usages of raspberry pi is less comparing to other micro controllers. It is widely used in many areas, such as for industries due to its, modularity and open design. </p>
